        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 7:10PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 710 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms 14 miles northeast of Kermit, moving west at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Notrees.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
